5px;">Ozy</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One question is: If you disguise your =
voice in order to impersonate a customer executive on a due diligence call =
in order to trick a=C2=A0potential investor into giving your company money,=
 <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25254005.273335/a=
HR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDktMjcvaW1w=
b3N0b3JzLW9uLXRoZS1kdWUtZGlsaWdlbmNlLWNhbGw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBbf0a33=
13" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;"> is that securities fraud</a>? I am not really a lawyer and no=
thing in this column is ever legal advice but =E2=80=A6=C2=A0yes? Yes, that=
 does seem very much like the core of securities fraud? Lying to people abo=
ut your business in order to trick them into investing money in your securi=
ties? So I=E2=80=99m going to go with yes.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=
Another question is: If you do that,=C2=A0and it doesn=E2=80=99t work, and =
<em>then</em> you don=E2=80=99t=C2=A0<em>disclose=C2=A0</em>to a=C2=A0<em>d=
ifferent=C2=A0</em>potential investor that you tried that on the first inve=
stor, is=C2=A0<em>that</em>=C2=A0securities fraud? That is, once you=E2=80=
=99ve done the fake diligence call, is every=C2=A0<em>subsequent=C2=A0</em>=
stock sale=C2=A0<em>also=C2=A0</em>fraud unless you say =E2=80=9Chey guys, =
just so you know, we tried a little fraud before but now we have stopped=E2=
=80=9D?</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It is a little harsh but I think th=
e answer is also yes? I am talking of course about Ozy Media, whose co-foun=
der Samir Rao allegedly <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/=
click/25254005.273335/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnl0aW1lcy5jb20vMjAyMS8wOS8yNi9idXNpb=
mVzcy9tZWRpYS9venktbWVkaWEtZ29sZG1hbi1zYWNocy5odG1s/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23=
cBeb3cbf05" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank=
" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-=
width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backg=
round-color: #ccc;">impersonated a YouTube executive</a> on a due diligence=
=C2=A0call with potential investors from Goldman Sachs Group Inc. about how=
 Ozy=E2=80=99s videos do on YouTube. Goldman quickly figured it out and pas=
sed on the investment so, no harm no foul I guess? Goldman did not sue anyw=
ay, though apparently Google (which owns YouTube) found out about the imper=
sonation and reported it to the FBI. But then Ozy kept going around trying =
to raise money, and it succeeded, and <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomber=
gbusiness.com/click/25254005.273335/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXd=
zL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMTAtMDUvb3p5LW1lZGlhLXN1ZWQtb3Zlci1jby1mb3VuZGVyLXMtZ2=
9sZG1hbi1jYWxsLWltcGVyc29uYXRpb24/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBe175e3b3" itempr=
op=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: =
#000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border=
-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;=
"> one of its later investors has now sued</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"=
margin: 16px 0;">Ozy Media Inc. was sued by an investor over its co-founder=
=E2=80=99s impersonation of a YouTube executive during a conference call wi=
th Goldman Sachs Group Inc. executives about a potential investment.</p><p =
style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">LifeLine Legacy Holdings LLC said in a securities=
 fraud suit filed late Monday that it invested around $2.25 million in Ozy =
in February and May partly because co-founders Carlos Watson and Samir Rao =
claimed Goldman was about to put money in the company.</p><p style=3D"margi=
n: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CWatson and Rao expressly represented to LifeLine that =
Goldman Sachs was positioning itself to make a substantial investment in th=
e company,=E2=80=9D Beverly Hills-based LifeLine said in its complaint file=
d in federal court in San Jose. =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">O=
zy never disclosed that =E2=80=9CRao attempted to impersonate an executive =
of YouTube in an effort to obtain a substantial investment from Goldman Sac=
hs, or that, as a result of Rao=E2=80=99s fraudulent conduct, Goldman Sachs=
 declined to invest in Ozy Media and that Ozy Media was under investigation=
 by government agencies,=E2=80=9D LifeLine said in its suit.</p></blockquot=
e><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Did it have to disclose that? Ozy is a priva=
te company, and when it sold stock to LifeLine it did so under a stock purc=
hase agreement, and a stock purchase agreement will generally contain a rep=
resentation saying something like =E2=80=9Cthe company complies with all ap=
plicable laws,=E2=80=9D and if you are currently doing a fraud, or recently=
 got finished doing a fraud, that rep is probably not true. Which makes the=
 new sale, arguably, also a fraud. From <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomb=
ergbusiness.com/click/25254005.273335/aHR0cHM6Ly9hc3NldHMuYndieC5pby9kb2N1b=
WVudHMvdXNlcnMvaXFqV0hCRmRmeElVL3JGZmRfMjR4WUFBOC92MA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a=
23cB62031b76" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bla=
nk" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-botto=
m-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; bac=
kground-color: #ccc;">LifeLine=E2=80=99s complaint</a>:</p><blockquote><p s=
tyle=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Based, in part, upon the foregoing representations=
, on or about February 24, 2021, LifeLine entered into a Series C Stock Pur=
chase Agreement (=E2=80=9CSeries C SPA=E2=80=9D) pursuant to which it agree=
d to purchase approximately $2 million of Series C Preferred Shares in Ozy =
Media.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Among other things, the Series C SPA=
 provided that =E2=80=9Cto the Company=E2=80=99s knowledge, the Company is =
not in violation of any federal or state statute, rule or regulation applic=
able to the Company=E2=80=9D.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=
In hindsight the proper approach would have been for Ozy=E2=80=99s lawyers =
to edit that rep to say =E2=80=9Cto the Company=E2=80=99s knowledge, the Co=
mpany is not in violation of any federal or state statute, rule or regulati=
on applicable to the Company; provided, however, that an executive of the C=
ompany did disguise his voice on a call with another potential=C2=A0investo=
r to impersonate a YouTube executive, which ended up getting reported to th=
e FBI, but that investor never actually invested and the executive was havi=
ng a tough time so we think it=E2=80=99s not really a big deal, but just FY=
I.=E2=80=9D That would have been fine I think. Though of course then LifeLi=
ne probably wouldn=E2=80=99t have invested? Which is the point? The point i=
s that this would have been material to LifeLine=E2=80=99s investment decis=
ion, had Ozy told them about it?=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anot=
her question is: Does Ozy exist, or what? Ozy announced last Friday that it=
 had <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25254005.2733=
35/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnl0aW1lcy5jb20vMjAyMS8xMC8wMS9idXNpbmVzcy9tZWRpYS9venkt=
bWVkaWEtY2FybG9zLXdhdHNvbi5odG1s/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBbe896c05" itempro=
p=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #=
000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-=
bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"=
>shut down</a>, but then its chief executive officer did a round of televis=
ion interviews Monday and Tuesday saying <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloom=
bergbusiness.com/click/25254005.273335/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xl=
cy9venktbWVkaWEtc2F5cy1pdC1wbGFucy10by1yZWxhdW5jaC1pbi1hYm91dC1mYWNlLTExNjM=
zMzcwNzU3P21vZD1ocF9saXN0YV9wb3M0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBf8c81f88" itempr=
op=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: =
#000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border=
-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;=
">actually nope it=E2=80=99s back</a>. Arguably it is a pleasant state for =
Ozy to be in, sort of shut down and sort of not. Do they get to choose from=
 moment to moment which it is? Go on TV: =E2=80=9CWe=E2=80=99re back and be=
tter than ever.=E2=80=9D Leave the set and get served with a lawsuit: =E2=
=80=9CNo no no no no, there=E2=80=99s no such thing as Ozy Media, it=E2=80=
=99s gone, poof.=E2=80=9D Maybe Ozy continues to exist as a brand but not a=
s a defendant in securities lawsuits?</p><table class=3D"liveintent-flex-ad=
